blog.name: wedontdowhisks
blog.title: tired and useless
blog.description: kip | bisexual

body:
Phil is not on fire

The video that started it all.

This world wasn’t originally meant to exist.

But it does.

Because of Phil is not on fire.

Can you believe it?

It’s been nine years.

Nine.

I haven’t been around for all of them.

Just the last two.

But I got to see Dan embrace his curls.

See him open up about his mental health.

See him become more comfortable with who he is.

I’ve gotten to see Phil embrace his quiff.

I’ve gotten to see him become more confident.

To see him be somehow more loving and caring.

I’ve seen both of them grow up in two years.

Not as much as some of you have over nine.

But it makes my chest hurt and it makes me happy and sad to have seen then grow up.

And for me it’s only been two years.

I can’t imagine how some of you feel who have been here for nine.

So cheers to you.

You’ve grown with them.

I think what I’ve seen grow the most, though

Isn’t the Phandom

It isn’t Dan

It isn’t Phil

It’s Dan and Phil

They’ve grown as friends

They know more about each other than most other people know about their best friends

They’ve set unrealistic goals for best friendship

But I still hope

That some day

I’ll find the Phil to my Dan

But one more thing before I go

Just a last thought

We’ll have many years to go

This isn’t the end

Let’s make it to 10

to 20

to 40

Let’s continue the whiskers and questions

Until we no longer can

Until sharpies either don’t exist or have killed us

Never feel childish or stupid for watching Dan and Phil

or for drawing whiskers on your noses

Because we have to make them proud

They’ve done so much for us

It’s time we repay them

So this year

year 9

draw whiskers on your face in black sharpie

ask questions

Rewatch old videos

and remember

This wasn’t supposed to happen

But it did
